\par\pard\plain \fi288\sb240\sl480\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 <$Scr_Ps::0>Mik sat on a bench in the hallway, along with a handful of other kids. No one talked. They were just trying to keep it together at this point and desparately wanted not to show too much emotion to other kids. The door opened and a girl from his math class walked out. She had a little smile on her face \hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1  not too bad, it said. A hand waived him in from inside, a disembodied voice said \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Mik.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 He walked in to see a man he had never met sitting behind a desk.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Ferd Cragen,\u8221\'94 the man said, as if that explained everything. \u8220\'93Have a seat.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Cragen made a show of finding Mik\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s record on his puter, as if it were some incredible feat of detective work.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Ah, here we are. OK, so we have our results. Huh, interesting. It suggests marketing, logistics, or AI interfacer. What do you think of that?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Yeah, that\u8217\'92s great,\u8221\'94 Mik said, relieved that none of them were his parents\u8217\'92 favorites. \u8220\'93Do I have to tell you now?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93No, not at all. In fact, these are just suggestions and we need to talk about them. It\u8217\'92s actually an unusual combination \hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1  only 3% of students got the same 3 choices. But hey, it\u8217\'92s a new century ahead and we need to walk some new paths, eh? Tell me what you think about them, what interests you about them.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 This felt like a trap, so he paused, trying to keep his face thoughtful. He wouldn\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92t reveal his cards totally. \u8220\'93Well, I can see why they choose that for me. I\u8217\'92m usually good with numbers and logic, so that explains marketing and logistics. And I\u8217\'92m good at patterns, too, so that must be why they suggested AI interfacer.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Patterns, eh?\u8221\'94 Cragen said quizically. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m not sure I see what you\u8217\'92re getting at.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Well, the AI uses algorithms to analyze and decide stuff. Algorithms are based on patterns \hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1  if this, then that. My mind kind of works like that, too, at least that\u8217\'92s what some of my teachers have told me. Sometimes AIs don\u8217\'92t see things that don\u8217\'92t belong in the pattern, things a person could see. A person like me. It\u8217\'92s a challenge \hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1  it\u8217\'92s basically a \u8220\'93what doesn\u8217\'92t belong\u8221\'94 or \u8220\'93what\u8217\'92s wrong with this picture\u8221\'94 sort of thing. I enjoy that.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93OK, that\u8217\'92s a novel way to look at it, but I see where you\u8217\'92re coming from. It\u8217\'92s not just statistics to you, it\u8217\'92s a picture.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Sort of.\u8221\'94 He could see Cragen was trying to goad him into saying he was smarter than the AI. \u8220\'93I mean the AI works with stats and all sorts of analyses that are way beyond me. I\u8217\'92m just saying when it spits out its result, I tend to see a pattern that it\u8217\'92s created. And you can go from there, to ask if that pattern is useful or matches everyday experience. Like I saw the pattern in the three choices the AI is giving me. Maybe it\u8217\'92s an odd combo \hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1  you would know that of course. But to me, I could see the logic, the pattern.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Well, apparently the AI could see that in you, too,\u8221\'94 Cragen said in an overly cheery voice. \u8220\'93It sounds like you\u8217\'92re most enthusiastic about the AI interface job. Tell me how you see that working in, say, 2110.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Again with the new century, Mik thought. Give it a rest!}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Gee, I hadn\u8217\'92t thought about that too much,\u8221\'94 Mik said. \u8220\'93But I know that some of the interfacers become AI engineers, getting deeper into the code and helping improve it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Yet you\u8217\'92re not rated here for software engineer.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93True. I know I would have to study more on that. I could learn on the job.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Perhaps,\u8221\'94 Cragen said. \u8220\'93The trend now, though, is to have the AI write its own code.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 This was news to him. }{\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93So what would be the next step up from AI interfacer?\u8221\'94 Mik asked. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Still evolving. But if I had to guess, it would be human engineering.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Mik hadn\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92t heard that phrase before. \u8220\'93Oh, interesting. We didn\u8217\'92t learn about that yet in school, What\u8217\'92s it about?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s about engineering processes and policies and rules that make it more likely that people will do the right thing without even having to think too hard about it. That\u8217\'92s what the next century is going to be all about. Right now, for example, we\u8217\'92re working with fishing villages in Asia to improve their productivity. In Hum Eng, they\u8217\'92re looking at what incentives are most attractive to the those people: money, goods, security, or something they discover that wasn\u8217\'92t apparent. Or it might be disincentives: fines for not making quotas and so on. And then the AIs can do all the crunching to come up with the amounts of money or quotas or whatever that will be most effective.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Fascinating. Sure, I could see myself doing that in a few years.\u8221\'94 A few hundred years, he thought. He couldn\u8217\'92t wait for this to be over.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93What attracts you to it?\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Freakin\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92 New Kendall, Mik thought. They never just take yes for an answer. It has to be yes for the right reason, meaning their reason. Tread carefully, he thought. \u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s another pattern, isn\u8217\'92t it? Those fishing people, their life has patterns, too. It would be fun to figure out what makes them go.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Mik sensed he had found an answer that was neither what Cragen wanted to hear nor one he could really argue against. Cragen seemed stuck on pause for a minute.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Okay,\u8221\'94 Cragen said. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92ve noted that here. We\u8217\'92ll let the people in AI interface know that. If you decide to go that route, they can mentor you toward that. Do you want to choose now?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Could I take some time? Like to talk to my folks, make sure for myself.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Absolutely. We\u8217\'92ll need your answer by the end of the month. And of course, we\u8217\'92re always here to help.  I\u8217\'92ve sent my info to your Voice, should you want to talk further. Otherwise, we\u8217\'92re done here.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 And with that, he ushered Mik out, passing the next lamb to slaughter on the way.}
